          "username": "Irina and Ethan",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "100746761633769805891",
          "user_review_count": 26,
          "user_photo_count": 3,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInC-l2-uIYR_paaLoEAZw_sPOFF4io26GPeMH9ybf18LQQjg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I am very happy with the way the surgery went. Dr. Zoland is a very talented surgeon, and I couldn't be happier that he was recommended to me and performed my procedure. The facility is very clean, everything ran on time like a well-oiled machine, and everyone was incredibly helpful and attentive. At some point after my IV was inserted, I started feeling light-headed (something that happens to me due to my fear of needles), so I called for help and a nurse came in right away \u2014 she lifted me up, gave me a button to press if I needed assistance again, and chatted with me until I felt better and the feeling passed entirely. The anesthesiologist and the surgeon were also very thorough in explaining the process, which made me feel supported, calm, and ready for the procedure.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21jMWR6WmxWRWRqWlVGWlVtSmZkbEJhWlZoVlVGRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x38db95f33c077657!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmc1dzZlVEdjZUFZUmJfdlBaZVhVUFE%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a month ago",
